race.comment: JENNI INTIBA (12) is having her first run for the Shane Jackson yard, formerly with Charlotte Littlefield. She's trialled since her last start placing at Sale behind the in-form Zambardo who has won easily in town since. She's open to improvement and should run a strong race. ARISTONOUS (2) worked home well first up at Sandown Hillside, also behind Zambardo, beaten five lengths by that horse. He hasn't won for a while but his best form is very good for a race like this and he'll strip fitter. RASP (10) knocked off his maiden easily two back and was good again last time over this route in a similar race. Tough draw but warrants respect again. AMIZETTA (6) resumes. She'll get further but this is a good kick off and the yard must be respected.
